{
  "text": "The diaphragm is also assumed to be made of linearly elastic, homogeneous and isotropic material. The effects of shear deformation and rotary inertia are neglected. The Kirchhoff theory of plates is used to model the elastic thin circular diaphragm. For a circular diaphragm with initial tension, the equation of motion for transverse displacement, w, of the diaphragm is [CITATION_1] ",
